
  1. Download two tarballs from https://developer.nvidia.com/embedded/jetson-linux-r3560:
    - Jetson_Linux_R35.6.0_aarch64.tbz2 (BSP — bootloader, kernel, flash tools)
    - Tegra_Linux_Sample-Root-Filesystem_R35.6.0_aarch64.tbz2 (Ubuntu 20.04 rootfs)
  2. Extract the BSP, which creates Linux_for_Tegra/ on the host.
  3. Extract the rootfs into Linux_for_Tegra/rootfs/.
  4. Run apply_binaries.sh to overlay Nvidia drivers/firmware into the rootfs.
  5. Put the Jetson into recovery mode (the device must be connected to the host via USB).
  6. Run flash.sh with the appropriate board config to write the images to the device.

  tar xf Jetson_Linux_R35.6.0_aarch64.tbz2
  cd Linux_for_Tegra/rootfs
  sudo tar xpf ../../Tegra_Linux_Sample-Root-Filesystem_R35.6.0_aarch64.tbz2
  cd ..
  sudo ./apply_binaries.sh
  sudo ./flash.sh ${board_config} mmcblk0p1
